# backend/.dockerignore — 1.9.0 W1 (QA-DEBT hygiene).
# The Dockerfile COPYies explicit paths (app/, alembic/, tests/, scripts/), so this
# file mostly shrinks the build-context upload: without it the local .venv (~hundreds
# of MB) and tool caches are shipped to the daemon on every build.
# NOTE: tests/ is still copied into the image on purpose (CI runs them in-container);
# dropping tests + dev deps from the PROD image is the 1.9.1 multi-stage work (SEC-DEPS-1).

.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
*.egg-info/
.env
*.log

# iCloud sync duplicates (QA-DEBT-1)
* [0-9]
* [0-9].*
